Instruction.1: While holding the upper arms stationary, curl the weights forward while contracting the biceps as you breathe out.
Instruction.2: Continue the movement until your biceps are fully contracted and the bar is at shoulder level.
Instruction.3: Hold the contracted position for a second and squeeze the biceps hard.
Instruction.4: Slowly bring the weight back down to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Take a double overhand grip that's about shoulder width. Flex your elbows while keeping your elbows tucked in. Try not to let them flare out.
Instruction.2: Curl until your forearm presses into your bicep. Then fully extend your elbows at the bottom of each rep.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing it with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with a neutral grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing it with your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Position a barbell in a landmine or corner of a room and stand facing sideways with a staggered stance and your feet shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Grasp the end of the barbell with an overhand grip, keeping your arms straight and your shoulders relaxed.
Instruction.3: Bend at the hips and knees to lower your torso until it is almost parallel to the ground.
Instruction.4: Pull the barbell towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blades together as you row the weight up.

Instruction.1: Start hinged forward with a flat back and the plates resting on the floor. Make sure your elbows are fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull the bar to your sternum.
Instruction.3: Return the plates back to the floor and let the bar come to a full dead stop.
Instruction.4: Then initiate the next rep.

Instruction.1: Grab the barbell with an overhand grip. Hinge forward while keeping your back flat until your torso is about parallel with the ground.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang freely.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your torso while tucking your elbows in slightly.
Instruction.4: Extend your elbows fully before initiating the next rep.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a barbell with your feet about hip-width apart and your palms facing towards your body.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grab the barbell with a pronated (overhand) grip, positioning the barbell about an inch away from your shins.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, use your back muscles to lift the barbell straight up towards your chest.
Instruction.4: As the barbell reaches your chest, rotate your wrists so that your palms are facing towards your body (supinated grip), and then lower the barbell back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a barbell with your feet about hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grab the barbell with a supinated (underhand) grip, positioning the barbell about an inch away from your shins.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, use your back muscles to lift the barbell straight up towards your chest.
Instruction.4: As the barbell reaches your chest, pause briefly, and then lower the barbell back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand beside the landmine with your feet shoulder-width apart while grasping the end of the landmine barbell with the hand farther away from the landmine attachment, palm facing up and your elbow close to your side.
Instruction.2: Curl the barbell up towards your opposite shoulder, contracting your bicep muscles, then slowly lower the barbell back down.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Start on one knee facing the landmine, holding the end of the barbell with your hand on the side of your forward leg.
Instruction.2: While keeping your elbow braced against the inside of your knee, curl the barbell upward towards your shoulder, then lower it back down with control.
Instruction.3: Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.

Instruction.1: Grab a barbell with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight back and let the bar drag against your upper body (or very close to it).

Instruction.1: Grab a v bar and place it under the bar's collar.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward with a flat back and pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Fully extend your elbows before initiating the next rep.

Instruction.1: Grab a barbell with a shoulder width pronated or supinated grip.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips while maintaining a flat back.
Instruction.3: Pull the weight toward your upper abdomen.
Instruction.4: Lower the weight in a controlled manner and repeat.

Instruction.1: Position yourself on preacher bench; grasp EZ bar with underhand grip, elbows extended.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl bar towards shoulders; keep upper arms stationary, focus on biceps.
Instruction.3: Lower bar back to starting position; maintain control, repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Sit on preacher bench, grip EZ bar overhand at shoulder width, elbows resting on pad.
Instruction.2: Curl bar towards chin, keep elbows stable.
Instruction.3: Lower bar slowly to starting position, maintaining control throughout.

Instruction.1: Use the V Bar attachment.
Instruction.2: Hold the attachment as you sit on the machine and put your legs under the leg pads.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your clavicle, then raise back up until your arm are extended.

Instruction.1: Use the Straight Bar attachment. Hold with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Hold the attachment as you sit on the machine and put your legs under the leg pads.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your clavicle, then raise back up until your arm are extended.

Instruction.1: Sit with your back straight on the machine and grip the handles.
Instruction.2: Pull the handles back using your arms. Your legs and torso should be at a 90° angle. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handles towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

Instruction.1: Use the Straight Bar attachment.
Instruction.2: Hold the attachment as you sit on the machine and put your legs under the leg pads.
Instruction.3: Pull the bar to your clavicle, then raise back up until your arm are extended.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust weight for assistance. Stand on platform, grip handles above shoulder-width. Knees on pad if available.
Instruction.2: Slowly pull up until chin is above the bar. Keep elbows close, core engaged.
Instruction.3: Lower back with control. Pause at bottom. Repeat for reps.

Instruction.1: Sit on the machine, feet flat, and grab the handles with palms facing up, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.2: Pull handles towards your lower abdomen, squeezing your shoulder blades together. Keep elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to the starting position, fully extending your arms without locking elbows. Repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Adjust the seat to fit your height and place your elbows on the elbow pad.
Instruction.2: Grab the handles and flex your elbows.

Instruction.1: Grip the handles with the palms facing down.
Instruction.2: Sit on the machine and press your knees into the knee pad.
Instruction.3: Pull the handles until your upper arm is even with your torso, or just behind your torso.
Instruction.4: Extend until your elbows are fully extended before initiating the next rep.

WorkoutName: Machine Seated Plate Loaded Preacher Curl

Instruction.1: Sit at the bench and rest the back of your arms on the preacher bench.
Instruction.2: Grab the handles. Curl the weight up until your elbows are fully flexed.
Instruction.3: Lower until the point just before the weight rests at the bottom.

WorkoutName: Machine Standing Plate Loaded Preacher Curl

Instruction.1: Rest the back of your arms on the preacher bench.
Instruction.2: Grab the handles. Curl the weight up until your elbows are fully flexed.
Instruction.3: Lower until the point just before the weight rests at the bottom.

Instruction.1: Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Instruction.2: Raise your arms out to your sides, bringing them up to shoulder level.
Instruction.3: Rotate your palms so they are facing the ceiling.
Instruction.4: Then, change direction and rotate the arms as much as you can.

Instruction.1: Stand an arms width away from the wall.
Instruction.2: Raise your arms out behind you, and place them on the wall with your fingers pointing up.
Instruction.3: Bend your knees whilst keeping your hands in the same position.

Instruction.1: Bend your arm at the elbow, raising your hand to your shoulder.
Instruction.2: Using your other hand, stretch the arm down to its full extent.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the wall, an arm's width away.
Instruction.2: Place your hand on the wall with your fingers pointing down.
Instruction.3: Lean slightly into the wall to feel the stretch in your bicep.

Instruction.1: Stand one foot in front of the other with the wall to your right, an arms width away.
Instruction.2: Place your hand on the wall, fingers pointing away from you.
Instruction.3: Gently lean forward, keeping your hand stationary.
Instruction.4: Repeat with the other arm.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the torso, palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Curl the plate up to the front of the shoulder while keeping the elbows close to the body.
Instruction.3: Rotate the palms to face forward and press the plate overhead, locking out the arms.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back to the starting position, keeping control of it, and repeat for desired reps.

WorkoutName: Plate Curl To Overhead Press To Tricep Extension

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and the plate in front of the torso, palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Curl the plate up to the front of the shoulder while keeping the elbows close to the body.
Instruction.3: Rotate the palms to face forward and press the plate overhead, locking out the arms.
Instruction.4: Lower the plate back behind the head to the starting position of a tricep extension.
Instruction.5: Push the plate back up overhead, then lower it back to the starting position and repeat for desired reps.

Instruction.1: Lower into a squat position, keeping the plate at chest height.
Instruction.2: Slowly curl the plate towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body.
Instruction.3: Hold for a moment at the top of the curl before lowering the plate back to chest height.
Instruction.4: Repeat the curls as you hold the squat position.

Instruction.1: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at your hips while maintaining a flat back.
Instruction.3: Pull the plate toward your upper abdomen.
Instruction.4: Lower the weight in a controlled manner and repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your elbows straight back and let the bar drag against your upper body (or very close to it).

Instruction.1: Start hinged forward with a flat back. Make sure your elbows are fully extended.
Instruction.2: Pull the bar to your sternum.

Instruction.1: Begin by standing in front of a bar with your feet about hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Bend at the hips and knees to grab the bar with a supinated (underhand) grip, positioning the bar about an inch away from your shins.
Instruction.3: Keeping your back straight and your core engaged, use your back muscles to lift the bar straight up towards your chest.
Instruction.4: As the bar reaches your chest, pause briefly, and then lower the bar back to the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length.
Instruction.2: Raise one dumbbell and twist your forearm until it is vertical and your palm faces the shoulder.
Instruction.3: Lower to original position and repeat with opposite arm

Instruction.1: Hold the dumbbells with a neutral grip (thumbs facing the ceiling).
Instruction.2: Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height
Instruction.3: Return to starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the dumbbells with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it's more comfortable on your wrists.
Instruction.2: Flex at the elbows until your biceps touch your forearms. Try not to let your elbows flair outward.

Instruction.1: Hold the dumbbells with a neutral grip (thumbs facing the ceiling). Seated on an incline bench.
Instruction.2: Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height
Instruction.3: Return to starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench.
Instruction.2: Grab the dumbbells with a pronated (overhand) grip. You can do this exercise thumbless if it's more comfortable on your wrists.
Instruction.3: Flex at the elbows until your biceps touch your forearms. Try not to let your elbows flair outward.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench with your palms facing forward.
Instruction.2: Flex at the elbows until your forearms touch your biceps.
Instruction.3: When you hit the top of the movement, rotate your palms and then lower the dumbbells slowly.

Instruction.1: Start with a with a dumbbell in one hand and your elbow resting on the bench.
Instruction.2: From this starting position, curl the dumbbell up towards your shoulder, keeping your upper arm stationary on the bench.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline or preacher curl bench.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang freely off the edge of the bench.
Instruction.3: Fully flex your elbow and fully extend your elbow on each rep.

Instruction.1: Start by placing your forearms on a flat bench and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: From this starting position, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body and your core engaged.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower the dumbbells back down to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of repetitions.

Instruction.1: Start by standing with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Bring the dumbbells to your sides, with your palms facing inward and your elbows bent.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, curl the dumbbells up towards your shoulders while rotating your wrists so that your palms face your shoulders at the top of the movement.

Instruction.1: Sit on a flat bench with your feet flat on the floor and your back straight.
Instruction.2: Lean forward and place your elbow on the inside of your leg.
Instruction.3: Curl the dumbbell while keeping your elbow against your leg. Make sure to fully extend your elbow on each rep.

Instruction.1: The dumbbells should be set on the ground. Hinge forward while keeping a flat back.
Instruction.2: Pull one elbow back toward the ceiling and then return the dumbbell to the ground softly.
Instruction.3: Then pull with the other arm.

Instruction.1: Place one hand and one knee on a bench. Make sure you keep a flat back.
Instruction.2: Pull the dumbbell toward the ceiling.
Instruction.3: Make sure to avoid any jerking or rotating.

Instruction.1: Lay on an incline bench that is between 30-45 degrees high.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang freely. Pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: The dumbbells should be placed on the floor.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward with a flat back and grab the dumbbells.
Instruction.3: Pull both dumbbells back and your elbows toward the ceiling.
Instruction.4: Return the dumbbells back to the floor softly on each rep.

Instruction.1: Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a dumbbell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the dumbbell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Start by placing your elbow on one knee.
Instruction.2: Hold a dumbbell in your other hand, with your palm facing inwards towards your body.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the dumbbell up towards your chest, keeping your elbow close to your body and your core engaged.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet staggered and one hand on a bench/box. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat,  and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.
Instruction.3: Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet staggered and one hand on your knee. Hold a dumbbell in the opposing hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips, keeping the back flat, and eyes facing forward. The weight should hang directly below the shoulders.
Instruction.3: Start with an overhand grip, as you pull rotate the dumbbell. When your upper arm reaches your side your palm should be facing forward.

Instruction.1: Hinge forward at the hips while maintaining a flat back. Try to get your torso as close to parallel with the ground as your mobility will allow for.
Instruction.2: Let your arms hang in front of you. Pull your elbows back towards the ceiling while flaring your elbows outward.

Instruction.1: Sit at preacher bench, hold dumbbells in each hand with arm extended, palm facing up.
Instruction.2: Curl dumbbells towards shoulder, keeping upper arm stationary and elbows in.
Instruction.3: Lower dumbbell slowly back to start.

Instruction.1: Hold the dumbbells with an underhand grip. Seated on an incline bench.
Instruction.2: Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height
Instruction.3: Return to starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you). Use a dip belt and the let the weight hang between your legs.
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Hold the dumbbells with an underhand grip. Seated on a bench.
Instruction.2: Start with the dumbbells pointed toward the ceiling, then lower the dumbbells toward your sides.
Instruction.3: Fully extend your elbows, but don't let your upper arm fall behind your torso.

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Bench Braced Hammer Flat Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Take a neutral grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Bench Braced Hammer Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Take a neutral grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Flat Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.
Instruction.3: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.4: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Flat Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench with the back of your working arm pressed into the side of the bench. Keep your hips all the way up.
Instruction.2: Fully extend your elbow and feel a stretch through your bicep, then curl.
Instruction.3: Stop before the dumbbell is pointed at the ceiling to keep tension on your biceps.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Hammer Flat Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Use a hammer grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Hammer Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips down.
Instruction.2: Take a neutral grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Flat Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips pushed toward the ceiling.
Instruction.2: Use an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

WorkoutName: Dumbbell Single Arm Bench Braced Reverse Incline Curl

Instruction.1: Lay off the side of a bench and place the back off your arms on the edge of your bench. Keep your hips lowered toward the floor.
Instruction.2: Take an overhand grip. Fully extend your elbows and then flex the elbows.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Start with a neutral grip. Flex at the elbow. While flexing twist your palm. When you hit the top of the movement your palm should be facing upward.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine.
Instruction.3: Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Use a neutral grip thumb facing up pinky-facing down). Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height.
Instruction.2: On the same side as the working arm, step back and rotate outwards.
Instruction.3: Pull your elbow back while flaring your elbow out.

Instruction.1: Use a bar attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face the cable machine.
Instruction.3: Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a rope attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Use a neutral grip thumb facing up pinky-facing down). Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height.
Instruction.2: Start with an overhand grip. As you pull your elbow back, rotate your palm until it faces upward.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Sit on a bench facing away from the cable machine.
Instruction.3: Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.

WorkoutName: Cable Single Arm Underhand Grip Row

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a handle attachment. Face your palm upward.
Instruction.2: Pull the handle back using your arms. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handle towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

WorkoutName: Cable Single Arm Neutral Grip Row

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a handle attachment. Face your palm toward the midline of your body.
Instruction.2: Pull the handle back using your arms. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handle towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine and sit on the bench. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Use a neutral grip thumb facing up pinky-facing down). Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine and sit on the bench. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Instruction.3: Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Stand facing away from the cables and grab two handle attachments.
Instruction.2: Take a neutral grip, flex your elbows, and extend.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment set all the way to the top of the cable crossover machine.
Instruction.2: Walk a few steps away from the cable machine. Face your body sideways.
Instruction.3: Face your palm up toward the ceiling. Then pull your elbow in toward your rib cage.

Instruction.1: Place the cable at shoulder height. Use a row bar.
Instruction.2: Pull the handles back using your arms. Push out your chest.
Instruction.3: Pull the handles towards your body until your hands are beside your abdomen.

Instruction.1: Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set to about elbow height.
Instruction.2: Face away from the cable machine.
Instruction.3: Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.

Instruction.1: Hold the TRX straps with an underhand grip and lean back and away from the anchor point.
Instruction.2: Keep your elbows high as you flex your elbows. Pull your fists toward your forehead.

Instruction.1: Grab the TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point.
Instruction.2: Maintain a neutral grip. Flex your elbows and pull your fists to either sides of your temples.

Instruction.1: Stand facing the TRX straps and grasp the handles with both hands, palms facing away from your body.
Instruction.2: Walk back until the straps are taut, keeping your arms straight.
Instruction.3: Slowly curl your hands towards your shoulders, keeping your elbows close to your body.

Instruction.1: Grab the TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point until the strap is taut.
Instruction.2: Start with an overhand grip. Pull your elbows back and rotate your grip.
Instruction.3: By the time your elbows reach your side, your palms should be facing upwards.

Instruction.1: Hold the TRX strap with one hand.
Instruction.2: Lean back until the strap is taut. Fully extend your elbow.
Instruction.3: Pull your elbow behind the body. Make sure to avoid twisting. Try to keep your shoulders even.

WorkoutName: Core Stability 2 Opposite Shoulder Tap 4Pt Position

Instruction.1: Bring yourself to the 4 point position (on all fours). 90° angles at hips and shoulder and neutral spine.
Instruction.2: Lift your knees slightly off the ground supporting your weight on palms and toes.
Instruction.3: Maintain a toe placement roughly at shoulder width (the wider the leg stance the easier the exercise - the narrower the stance the more difficult it becomes.
Instruction.4: Tap your opposite shoulder with your fingertips.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight and hold a dumbbell in one arm. Perform a bicep curl across your body
Instruction.2: Bring the dumbbell to your shoulder and rotate palm and elbow out.
Instruction.3: Point the elbow towards the ceiling while the dumbbell remains just over the shoulder.
Instruction.4: Extend your elbow to raise the dumbbell over your head. Start lowering your arm to your side as you turn the palm to face down

Instruction.1: Abduct your arm at 90° palm facing down.
Instruction.2: Bend your elbow and wrist bringing your front of your fingertips to your temple while leaning the head towards the the arm.
Instruction.3: Lean the head away from the arm as you extend the elbow and flex the wrist.
Instruction.4: Alternate between positions to mobilise the ulnar nerve.

Instruction.1: Abduct your arm at 90° palm facing down.
Instruction.2: Bend your elbow and wrist to bring the palm to face the ceiling while leaning the head towards the opposite shoulder.
Instruction.3: Find the position of maximum tension (without pain) and hold.
Instruction.4: To increase the stretch, press the palm against the face and try to point the elbow up.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chin above the bar.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with an underhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chest to the bar.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with a mixed grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chin above the bar.

Instruction.1: Grasp the chin-up bar with an overhand grip, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Place your feet on the ground, legs bent slightly.
Instruction.3: Use your legs to assist as you pull your chin above the bar.

Instruction.1: Hang from a bar with your feet on the floor.
Instruction.2: Break at the elbows and curl your body towards the bar.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar with a close grip. Feet on the floor.
Instruction.2: Break at the elbow and curl your body toward the bar.

Instruction.1: Place your elbow on one knee and your hand underneath the other leg. Keep the leg that's over your hand extended.
Instruction.2: Curl the working arm and use your leg as the resistance.

Instruction.1: Lay underneath a fixed horizontal bar and grab the bar with an underhand grip.
Instruction.2: Pull your body straight up to the bar.
Instruction.3: Return to the starting position, your arms fully extended. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Set up rings at a high point.
Instruction.2: Grip rings and lean back, arms extended.
Instruction.3: Pull chest to rings, keeping body straight.

Instruction.1: Stand holding gymnastic rings with your arms extended in front of you, palms facing up.
Instruction.2: Curl rings towards shoulders, squeezing biceps.
Instruction.3: Slowly lower rings back to starting position, keeping control. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body in an "L" position and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the bar shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up and lean backwards. Try to touch your chest to the bar.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the rings shoulder width apart with a supinated grip (palms facing you)
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up until your chin is past the rings.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Grab the rings shoulder width apart with a pronated grip (palms facing away).
Instruction.2: With your body hanging and arms fully extended, pull yourself up and rotate your fists until your chin is past the rings.
Instruction.3: Slowly return to starting position. Repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis.
Instruction.2: Raise the kettlebell bending your arms at the elbow until the kettlebell is level with your chest.
Instruction.3: Lower to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Sitting on a chair with your legs apart, rest your arm against your thigh and hold the kettlebell with your arm extended towards the floor.
Instruction.2: Bending your arm at the elbow, lift the kettlebell until your palm faces your shoulder.
Instruction.3: Lower to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand behind a bench, with your chest leaning over the edge of the bench.
Instruction.2: With one arm resting on the bench, hold the kettlebell, bending the arm at the elbow.
Instruction.3: Lower your arm using the bench as a guide, keeping your forearm straight.
Instruction.4: Return to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand up straight with a kettlebell in one hand with your forearm facing out.
Instruction.2: Raise the kettlebell, bending your arm at the elbow and keeping your forearm vertical until your palm faces the shoulder.
Instruction.3: Lower to the starting position and repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Bend at hips, row kettlebell to chest.
Instruction.3: Alternate hands for each row.

Instruction.1: Grab two kettlebells, stand tall.
Instruction.2: Curl kettlebells toward chest.
Instruction.3: Lower kettlebells, repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with kettlebell between legs.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, grab kettlebell, pull to chest and rotate at the torso

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Hold kettlebell with palms facing down.
Instruction.3: Lift kettlebell toward shoulders, squeezing biceps, then lower with control.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, hold a kettlebell in each hand.
Instruction.2: Hinge at hips, keep back straight, and pull both kettlebells to hips.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Hold a kettlebell with palms facing down.
Instruction.3: Lift kettlebell toward shoulders, squeezing biceps, then lower with control.

WorkoutName: Kettlebell Single Arm Row On Bench

Instruction.1: Start by standing in front of a flat bench with your feet shoulder-width apart and holding a kettlebell in one hand.
Instruction.2: Place your other hand on the bench for support, and bend at the waist so that your chest is parallel to the ground.
Instruction.3: From this starting position, row the kettlebell up towards your chest, squeezing your shoulder blade together as you do so.
Instruction.4: Make sure to keep your elbow close to your body and your core engaged throughout the movement.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same hand as the leg shifted backwards.
Instruction.2: Bend forwards at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knee, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Instruction.2: Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Instruction.3: Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your upper chest and then lower the kettlebell- repeat.

Instruction.1: Stand with feet hip-width apart, kettlebell in each hand, hinge at hips.
Instruction.2: Pull kettlebells while flaring your elbows, squeezing shoulder blades. Keep back flat.

Instruction.1: Attach band to a low anchor point. Point your palms straight forward.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

Instruction.1: Attach band to a low anchor point. Use a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

Instruction.1: Attach band to a low anchor point. . Point your palms toward your thighs.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbow until you feel your biceps contract. Then fully extend elbows.

Instruction.1: Anchor a band to a high point.
Instruction.2: Start with your feet staggered and your elbows high.
Instruction.3: Flex your elbows while keeping your arms high. Curl the band to your forehead.

Instruction.1: Start with the band anchored to something high with your feet staggered and a neutral grip.
Instruction.2: Keep your elbows high. Curl until your fists are at your forehead.

Instruction.1: Start with a band attached to a high point, your feet staggered, and an overhand grip.
Instruction.2: Flex your elbows pulling your forearms to your biceps. Your fists should land by your forehead.

Instruction.1: Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart, with the band under both feet.
Instruction.2: Grasp the handles of the band with both hands, keeping your arms straight and extended in front of you.
Instruction.3: Keep your back straight, abs engaged, and shoulders relaxed as you curl your hands towards your shoulders, bending at the elbows.

Instruction.1: Start by standing on the center of the band with both feet, shoulder-width apart.
Instruction.2: Hold the band with both hands, palms facing down, arms extended straight in front of you.
Instruction.3: Slowly curl your hands towards your shoulders, pulling the band tight, then lower your arms back to the starting position, keeping tension on the band throughout the exercise.

Instruction.1: Place the band at about eye level. Fall into a kneeling position.
Instruction.2: The knee that is on the ground should be the same side as the working arm. Stick your chest out.
Instruction.3: And then pull your elbow straight back. Flex your lats and then extend into the starting position.

Instruction.1: Stand on your band with both feet.
Instruction.2: Hinge forward at the hips while keeping a flat back.
Instruction.3: Let your arms hang freely, then pull your elbows straight back toward the ceiling.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a stable point.
Instruction.2: Take a half squat position and hold there.
Instruction.3: Perform a row while holding the squat position.

WorkoutName: Band Squat Hold Single Arm Row

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a stable point and take a half squat position.
Instruction.2: Hold the band loop in one hand and pull your elbow straight back.

Instruction.1: Anchor band to a stable point.
Instruction.2: Step back until there is no slack in the band and hold the end of the band with one hand.
Instruction.3: Pull through the elbow straight back.

Instruction.1: Anchor the band to a high point. Go into a seated position.
Instruction.2: Grab the loop of the band and pull your upper arm to your side.

Instruction.1: Begin in a squatting position with your feet together and your knees apart.
Instruction.2: Place your hands on the floor in front of you, shoulder-width apart. Keep your arms straight and engage your core.
Instruction.3: Slowly shift your weight forward and lift your feet off the ground, coming onto your tiptoes.
Instruction.4: Bend your elbows and lean your weight onto your hands, shifting your knees towards your upper arms.
Instruction.5: Gently lift one foot off the ground, and then the other, balancing on your hands. Hold the pose for a few breaths before releasing back to the ground.

Instruction.1: Begin on your hands and knees with your hands shoulder-width apart and your knees hip-width apart.
Instruction.2: Spread your fingers wide and press down into your palms, making sure that your fingers are evenly spaced and facing forward.
Instruction.3: Tuck your toes under and lift your knees off the ground, straightening your legs as much as possible.
Instruction.4: Press your hips up and back, bringing your body into an inverted "V" shape.
Instruction.5: Keep your arms straight and your shoulder blades spread apart, and try to press your heels down towards the ground.
Instruction.6: Hold the pose for several breaths, then release and return to your starting position.

WorkoutName: Downward Dog With Fingers Facing Feet

Instruction.1: Begin in the same starting position as the previous exercise, with your hands and knees on the ground.
Instruction.2: Spread your fingers wide and turn your hands so that your fingers are facing towards your feet.
Instruction.3: Tuck your toes under and lift your knees off the ground, straightening your legs as much as possible.
Instruction.4: Press your hips up and back, bringing your body into an inverted "V" shape.
Instruction.5: Keep your arms straight and your shoulder blades spread apart, and try to press your heels down towards the ground.
Instruction.6: Hold the pose for several breaths, then release and return to your starting position.

Instruction.1: Begin in a downward-facing dog pose.
Instruction.2: Slowly lift one leg up towards the ceiling, keeping your hips level and your toes pointed.
Instruction.3: Bend your lifted leg and try to touch your toes to the back of your head.
Instruction.4: Once you have a firm grip with your toes, slowly begin to twist your torso towards the lifted leg.
Instruction.5: Keep your hands and feet firmly planted on the ground as you hold the pose for a few breaths. Release the pose and repeat on the other side.

Instruction.1: Sit cross-legged on the floor.
Instruction.2: Extend your arms straight out in front of you, palms facing forward.
Instruction.3: Cross your right arm over your left arm and interlace your fingers.
Instruction.4: Pull your hands away from your body and hold for a few breaths, then release and repeat with the opposite arm on top.

Instruction.1: Stand with a band looped under both feet and the band grasped in both hands.
Instruction.2: Do a light hop and bring your feet outward while simultaneously flexing the elbows.
Instruction.3: Bring both feet back together and extend the elbows.

Instruction.1: Sit on seat, feet strapped in, grip handle with arms extended.
Instruction.2: Push with legs, lean back slightly, pull handle to lower ribs.
Instruction.3: Extend arms, lean forward from hips, bend knees to return to start.

WorkoutName: Cardio Row Erg Rower Arms Only

Instruction.1: Make sure your feet are strapped in tightly.
Instruction.2: Without bending your legs, pull the handle to your ribcage.
Instruction.3: Fully extend your elbows before initiating the next rep.

WorkoutName: Cardio Row Erg Rower Four Stroke Sprint Start

Instruction.1: Sit on seat, feet strapped in, grip handle with arms extended.
Instruction.2: Push with legs, lean back slightly. Do four small pulls with increasing distance on each rep.
Instruction.3: Extend arms, lean forward from hips, bend knees to return to start.
